	<h3>How to calculate BAC</h3>
	<p>BAC can be calculated by examining a sample of blood (a difficult task to perform at home or at a party!) or by analyzing breath. The police have expensive breathalyzers capable of accurately calculating BAC.
	<Strong>To estimate your BAC, you need to know three simple facts: how much you drink, how fast you drink(amount of time you spend drinking), and how much you weigh (You also must know your gender!).</Strong>

	</p>
	<p> If needed, use the following to assist in computing BAC </br></p>
	<p> 1 pint 80 proof tequila = 13 standard drinks </br></p>
	<p> 1 pint 100 proof whiskey/vodka = 16 standard drinks </br></p>
	<p> 1 fifth 80 proof tequila = 22 standard drinks </br></p>
	<p> 1 fifth 100 proof whiskey/vodka = 27 standard drinks </br></p>
	<p> 1 quart of beer(32 oz.) = 3 standard drinks </br></p>
	<p> 1 fifth of wine = 7 standard drinks </br></p>
